# Introduction # {#introduction}

[=Transport Service Users=], [=Transport Service Organizers=], and [=Transport Operators=]
face a growing need to calculate and report logistics emissions with
greater accuracy and transparency. Increasingly, this means moving beyond default
and modeled data toward primary data that reflects actual operational emissions.

The methodological foundations for this shift are already in place: [[!ISO14083|ISO 14083:2023]]
and the [[!GLEC|GLEC Framework]] have established a shared basis for emissions accounting.
Yet data access processes remain largely manual and vary from company to company, making the
exchange of primary emissions data both challenging and costly.

The iLEAP Technical Specifications address this gap by enabling the structured flow of
emissions and activity data across organizations and IT systems. They do so by:

1. "working backwards" from concrete business cases ([[#business-cases]]),
2. translating those business cases into well-defined data transactions ([[#txns]])
    that can be realized through independent software implementations,
    known as [=host systems=],
3. defining a data exchange protocol ([[#http-rest-api]]) to unlock the interoperable
      flow of data between host systems, and
4. introducing a data model ([[#data-model]]) that aligns with [[!ISO14083|ISO 14083]] and the [[!GLEC|GLEC Framework V3.1]].


## Methodological Interoperability ## {#interop}

Issue: This section might need further elaboration.

The iLEAP Technical Specifications are based on [[!ISO14083|ISO14083:2023]],
with which they are methodologically aligned and the [[!GLEC|GLEC Framework V3.1]].

Furthermore, the specifications are designed to be methodologically interoperable
with the [[!PACT-V2|PACT Methodology Version 2]] and [[!PACT-V3|Version 3]].


## PACT Technical Interoperability ## {#pact-interop}

iLEAP is interoperable with the [[!PACTDX|PACT Data Exchange Protocol]]
and its PCF data model ([[#pcf-mapping]]).

With v1.1.0, the [=iLEAP standalone protocol=] ([[#http-rest-api]])
is introduced as the primary protocol for data exchange, while support
for the [[!PACTDX|PACT Data Exchange Protocol]] is maintained for backward
compatibility and fallback purposes.

Note: The PACT Data Exchange Protocol integration is scheduled for removal with the v2.0.0 release of the iLEAP Technical Specifications.

Note: The editors of this specification strive to assert semantical interoperability with the PACT Technical Specifications with future releases.


## Out of Scope ## {#out-of-scope}

Note: Non-normative section

These specifications do not cover the following topics or aspects, as they are covered elsewhere or declared as out of scope of this specification:

1. Methodology for the calculation of logistics-related emissions. The technical specifications' normative foundations are the [[!GLEC]] Framework and [[!ISO14083]].
1. Black Carbon Methodological and Accounting principles.
1. Technical details on capturing necessary data for primary data-based calculations approaches, such as data collection with or through telematics systems, TMS, etc.
1. Contracts or legal aspect of data exchange between parties, including third party entities offering digital services or tools.
1. Auditing and verification of actual emissions calculations beyond systems-level accreditation.
      Verification-related properties are expected to be included in future versions of these technical specifications.
1. Transparency relating to market-based or project accounting approaches and measures.
      Book and claim-related approaches are expected to be included in future versions of these technical specifications.
1. Variables for detailed GHG emissions modeling, as described in [[!ISO14083]], Section 13.4.3 and Annex M. The current data model focuses on enabling primary data collection. Basic use of modeled and default data is supported, but detailed parameters remain excluded.
1. Modes of transport "cable car" and "pipeline".
1. Refrigerant emissions, as described in [[!ISO14083]], Annex I. These will be incorporated in future versions of these technical specifications.
1. Reporting with per-modality transparency as defined in Section 13.3 of [[!ISO14083]].
    The key difference between this approach and iLEAP is that the former also <i>allows</i> for a) aggregating over more than 1 shipment, and b) disclosing emissions per modality.
    The iLEAP Technical Specifications operate on a per-shipment and per-TCE basis.
    However, <i>transparency at this level is implicitly assumed by ISO14083 Chapter 13.3 (when aggregating over multiple shipments)</i>.
    Comprehensive reporting according to [[!ISO14083]] Chapter 13.3 is expected to be included in future versions of these technical specifications.

## Document Statuses ## {#document-statuses}

The iLEAP Technical Specifications adhere to the [SemVer](https://semver.org/) standard and are
published according to a flow that clearly distinguishes work-in-progress from pre-releases and
stable releases. These are indicated by the status tag below at the top of the document. Possible
status tags are:

: Living Document

:: Work-in-progress. The version number is typically extended with the date on which the most recent
    changes were made (e.g., 0.2.1-20240523). Accessible at
    [https://specs.ileap.global/](https://specs.ileap.global/).

: Consultation Draft

:: Pre-release. Distributed for the purpose of obtaining community feedback. No further significant
    changes will be made until the release. Minor corrections may still be possible. Every
    Consultation Draft is assigned a stable, permanent, URL, e.g.,
    [https://specs.ileap.global/TR/2024/ileap-extension-20240521/](https://specs.ileap.global/TR/2024/ileap-extension-20240521/).

: Release

:: Stable release. No further changes will be made to this version. Any additional changes will be
    included in subsequent versions. Every Release is assigned a stable, permanent, URL, e.g.,
    [https://specs.ileap.global/TR/2024/ileap-extension-20240605/](https://specs.ileap.global/TR/2024/ileap-extension-20240605/).


