# Data Model # {#data-model}

The iLEAP data model of this chapter together with the data transactions ([[#txns]]) build upon
[[!ISO14083|ISO 14083]] and the [[!GLEC|GLEC Framework]]. The purpose of the data model is to
define the syntax and semantics with the goal of enabling the interoperable exchange of data
between a [=data owner=] and a [=data recipient=] using the HTTP REST API ([[#http-rest-api]]).

The data model is composed of six main data types organized into two categories.

The first category covers **emissions data** aligned with [[!ISO14083|ISO 14083]]. At its
foundation are the data types <{TCE}>, <{TOC}>, and <{HOC}>, corresponding to the ISO 14083
concepts of [=Transport Chain Element|TCE=], [=TOC=], and [=HOC=]. Building on these,
the data model defines two complementary approaches to emissions reporting in line with
ISO 14083 reporting principles: <{ShipmentFootprint}>, which represents the footprint of an
individual shipment across its [=TC|transport chain=], and <{AR|AggregatedReport}>, which
facilitates the exchange of aggregated emissions data, e.g. for reporting to public authorities
and to avoid disclosing sensitive data.

The second category covers **activity data**. <{TAD}> (transport activity data, [[#dt-tad|TAD]])
enables reporting in case of missing data or limited emissions calculation capabilities from e.g.
[=Transport Operators=].

<{ShipmentFootprint|ShipmentFootprints}>, <{TOC|TOCs}>, and <{HOC|HOCs}> can also be embedded as
data extensions in the PACT Data Model ([[!PACTDX]]) (see [[!DATA-MODEL-EXTENSIONS]] and
[[#pcf-mapping]]) in a `ProductFootprint`.


<div class="advisement" id="M*" style="text-align: center">
  <strong>Properties marked with `M*` are required when using the [=iLEAP standalone protocol=], but
  optional when exchanging iLEAP data as a PACT Data Model Extension, as they are already required in
  the PACT Data Model (see [[#pcf-mapping]]).</strong>
</div>


## ShipmentFootprint ## {#dt-sf}

The <dfn element>ShipmentFootprint</dfn> data type enables reporting at the
level of transport or hub services for a single shipment, aligned with
[[!ISO14083|ISO 14083]] (Chapter 13.3) and the [[!GLEC|GLEC Framework]].

A ShipmentFootprint covers one or more [=Transport Chain Elements=] and
their respective emissions, encoded as <{TCE|TCEs}>. By collecting one or
more ShipmentFootprints, a [=Transport Chain=] ([=TC=]) and its emissions
data can be assembled together ultimately enabling the calculation of the
shipment's logistics emissions.

Note: A ShipmentFootprint CAN include TCEs that the [=data owner=] collected from other parties.

### Data Attributes ### {#sf-attributes}

A <{ShipmentFootprint}> has the following properties:

Issue: Consider adding
[declaredUnit](https://wbcsd.github.io/tr/2024/data-exchange-protocol-20240410/#element-attrdef-carbonfootprint-declaredunit)

<figure id="sf-properties-table" dfn-type="element-attr" dfn-for="ShipmentFootprint">
  <table class="data">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Property
        <th>Type
        <th>Req
        <th>Specification
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><dfn>specVersion</dfn>
        <td>String
        <td>[M*](#M*)
        <td>
            The version of the iLEAP Technical Specifications to which the data conforms, expressed as a string in the format `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`, following Semantic Versioning 2.0.0 (see [[!SEMVER]]).

            For the present version, the value MUST be `1.1.0`.
      <tr>
        <td><dfn>companyName</dfn>
        <td>String
        <td>[M*](#M*)
        <td>
            The name of the company owning the data.
      <tr>
        <td><dfn>companyIds</dfn>
        <td>String[]
        <td>O
        <td>

            The non-empty set of strings where each value uniquely identifies the [=data owner=].

            Issue: add coding examples, possibly including URN-based encodings aligning with PACT's or other approaches.
            Community input needed on the preferred approach to encoding company identifiers: URN vs UUID, e.g.
      <tr>
        <td><dfn>description</dfn>
        <td>String
        <td>O
        <td>
            A description of the Shipment.
      <tr>
        <td><dfn>createdAt</dfn>
        <td>String
        <td>[M*](#M*)
        <td>
            Timestamp of the creation of the <{ShipmentFootprint}>.
      <tr>
        <td><dfn>status</dfn>
        <td>String
        <td>M
        <td>
            Each <{ShipmentFootprint}> MUST include the property `status` with value one of the following
            values:

            : `Active`
            :: The default `status` of a <{ShipmentFootprint}> is `Active`. A <{ShipmentFootprint}> with status Active CAN be used by data recipients for logistics emissions calculations.
            : `Deprecated`
            :: The <{ShipmentFootprint}> SHOULD NOT be used for logistics emissions calculations by data recipients.
      <tr>
        <td><dfn>referencePeriodStart</dfn>
        <td>String
        <td>[M*](#M*)
        <td>
            Timestamp of the start (including) of the time boundary for which the data is considered to be representative.

            The value MUST be a date and time string conforming to ISO 8601 with timezone UTC.

            This start date represents the earliest date from which activity data was collected to include in the emissions calculation.

            Issue: Needs revision
      <tr>
        <td><dfn>referencePeriodEnd</dfn>
        <td>String
        <td>[M*](#M*)
        <td>
            Timestamp of the end (excluding) of the time boundary for which the data is considered to be representative.

            The value MUST be a date and time string conforming to ISO 8601 with timezone UTC.

            This end date represents the latest date until which activity data was collected to include in the emissions calculation.

            Issue: Needs revision
      <tr>
        <td><dfn>secondaryEmissionFactorSources</dfn>
        <td>Object[]
        <td>O
        <td>
            The non-empty set of the secondary emission factor sources used for the calculation of the emissions data.

            Each element of the array MUST be an object with the following properties:

            - `name`: String, M, The name of the source.
            - `version`: String, O, The version of the source.

            Issue: proposed attribute pending community input
      <tr>
        <td><dfn>pactPds</dfn>: Decimal
        <td>String
        <td>O
        <td>
            The share of primary data in percent used for the calculation of the emissions data, expressed as a value between 0 and 100 (both inclusive), as defined in the PACT Methodology v3.

            Issue: proposed attribute pending community input
      <tr>
        <td><dfn>comment</dfn>
        <td>String
        <td>O
        <td>
            Additional information related to the Shipment.

            SHOULD be used for information and instructions related to the calculation of the data, or other information which informs the ability to interpret, to audit or to verify it.

            Issue: proposed attribute pending community input
      <tr>
        <td><dfn>mass</dfn> : [=Decimal=]
        <td>String
        <td>M
        <td>The mass of the good (in `kilograms`) and the packaging provided for transport by the [=Transport Service User=], excluding any additional packaging or handling equipment used by the Transport Operator or Transport Service Organizer.
      <tr>
        <td><dfn>volume</dfn> : [=Decimal=]
        <td>String
        <td>O
        <td>The volume of the freight (in `cubic metres`) and any packaging provided by the [=Transport Service User=].
      <tr>
        <td><dfn>shipmentId</dfn>
