## Action AggregatedEmissionsData ## {#action-aed}

Lists the [=data owner=]'s <{AggregatedReports}> with REQUIRED [[#access-control]], REQUIRED [[#pagination]], and OPTIONAL [[#filtering]].

Note:
  To retrieve `AggregatedReports` based on embedded properties (regardless of the level of nesting),
  [=data recipients=] SHOULD use [[#filtering]]. See [[#action-aed-request-examples]] for examples.

### Request Syntax ### {#action-aed-request}

<pre highlight=http>
  GET <l>[=Subpath=]</l>/v1/ileap/aed?<l>[=Filter=]</l>&<l>[=Limit=]</l> HTTP/1.1
  host: <l>[=Hostname=]</l>
  authorization: Bearer <l>[=BearerToken=]</l>
</pre>

#### Examples #### {#action-aed-request-examples}

To retrieve all `AggregatedReports`:

<div class=example>

  ```http
  GET /v1/ileap/aed HTTP/1.1
  ```
</div>

To retrieve a single `AggregatedReport`, identified by <{AggregatedReport/reportId}> equal to `"report-1"`:

<div class=example>
  ```http
  GET /v1/ileap/aed?reportId=report-1 HTTP/1.1
  ```
</div>

To retrieve `AggregatedReports` with <{AggregatedReport/perModeEmissions}> including the <{ModeSpecificReport/transportMode}> `"Rail"`

<div class=example>
  ```http
  GET /v1/ileap/aed?perModeEmissions.mode=rail HTTP/1.1
  ```
</div>

### Response Syntax ### {#action-aed-response}

Non-paginated response:

<pre highlight=http>
  HTTP/1.1 <l>[=StatusCode=]</l> <l>[=StatusText=]</l>
  content-type: application/json
  content-length: <l>[=ContentLength=]</l>

  <l>[=ResponseBody=]</l>
</pre>

Paginated response ([[#pagination]]):

<pre highlight=http>
  HTTP/1.1 <l>[=StatusCode=]</l> <l>[=StatusText=]</l>
  content-type: application/json
  content-length: <l>[=ContentLength=]</l>
  link: <l>[=PaginationLink=]</l>; rel="next"

  <l>[=ResponseBody=]</l>
</pre>

#### Example #### {#action-aed-response-examples}

<div class=example>
  Example response to request with `limit=1`

  ```http
  HTTP/1.1 200 OK
  content-type: application/json
  content-length: 1321
  link: <https://api.ileap.sine.dev/v1/ileap/aed?offset=1&limit=1>; rel="next"
  ```

  ```json
  {
    "data": [
      {
        "reportId": "ar-2025-q4-001",
        "shipmentIds": [
          "shipment-12345",
          "shipment-12346",
          "shipment-12347"
        ],
